From 9cbae2f95344bf9a3ff1334179e7101028f7d053 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brian Cain <brian.cain@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Mar 2026 11:33:44 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 07/13] [Hexagon] Guard HVXIEEEFP intrinsics with
 __HVX_IEEE_FP__
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="utf-8"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The C intrinsic header hvx_hexagon_protos.h only guarded the 53
HVXIEEEFP intrinsics by architecture version (__HVX_ARCH__ >= 68/73/79),
making them visible even when IEEE FP is not enabled. Add
defined(__HVX_IEEE_FP__) to each guard so the intrinsics are only
available when the extension is active (+hvx-ieee-fp).
---
 clang/lib/Headers/hvx_hexagon_protos.h   | 212 +++++++++++------------
 clang/test/Headers/hexagon-hvx-headers.c |  39 +++++
 2 files changed, 145 insertions(+), 106 deletions(-)

